fields.name: Django
fields.summary: Django is a widely-used Python web framework with a "batteries-included" feature philosophy.

fields.name: Rollout
fields.summary: Rollout is a feature flipper for Ruby applications.

fields.name: Split
fields.summary: Split is an A/B testing and feature flipping library for Ruby applications.

fields.name: Vanity
fields.summary: Vanity is an A/B testing and feature flipping library for Ruby applications.

fields.name: Apache Ant
fields.summary: Apache Ant is a procedural build tool based on XML schemas. While it was originally inteded for Java projects, it can be used with any programming ecosystem.

fields.name: Apache Maven
fields.summary: Apache Maven is a package management system and build tool based on project object model (POM) files.

fields.name: Gradle
fields.summary: Gradle is a build system and automation tool for Java Virtual Machine languages.

fields.name: Bazel
fields.summary: Bazel is a build tool created by Google that is designed for minimizing build time.

fields.name: Dashing
fields.summary: Dashing is a framework for building sweet-looking dashboards with custom widgets.

fields.name: Flask
fields.summary: Flask is a Python micro web framework built with Werkzeug for routing, Jinja2 as a template engine and (optionally) SQL-Alchemy as the backend object-relational mapper.

fields.name: Python
fields.summary: Python is dynamically typed.

fields.name: Ada
fields.summary: Ada is an statically typed, imperative paradigm programming language.

fields.name: Swift
fields.summary: Swift is a multi-paradigm open source programming language originally developed by Apple.

fields.name: Regent
fields.summary: Regent is a language for implicit dataflow parallelism.

fields.name: CoffeeScript
fields.summary: CoffeeScript is a multi-paradigm language the transcompiles to JavaScript.

fields.name: Arc
fields.summary: Arc is a dialect of Lisp intended for exploratory programming.

fields.name: C
fields.summary: C is a statically-typed, imperative paradigm programming language. The language was originally created for implementing the Unix operating system but then grew to be one of the most widely used and influential programming language in computer science.

fields.name: C#
fields.summary: C# is a multi-paradigm programming language originally developed by Microsoft for its .NET platform.

fields.name: Ceylon
fields.summary: Ceylon is an open source, statically-typed object-oriented programming language that can create programs that run on the Java Virtual Machine or transcompiled to JavaScript.

fields.name: Clojure
fields.summary: Clojure is functional paradigm programming language heavily influenced by Lisp.

fields.name: COBOL
fields.summary: COBOL is a procedural and imperative paradigm programming language designed for business use. The language dates back to the 1950s and was standardized in 1968, being revised fouor times, most recently in 2014.

fields.name: C++
fields.summary: C++ is an imperative and object-oriented language that enhances the C programming language with classes and related features such as inheritance, templates and exceptions.

fields.name: Common Lisp
fields.summary: Common Lisp is a standardized dialect specification of the Lisp Programming Language. Several implementations of the specification are available.

fields.name: Ruby
fields.summary: Ruby is a dynamically typed multi-paradigm language that blends object-oriented and functional programming.

fields.name: Rust
fields.summary: Rust is a statically-typed language intended for concurrent and highly safe software programs.

fields.name: Red
fields.summary: Red is a functional programming language inspired by REBOL.

fields.name: Bash
fields.summary: Bash, the Bourne Again SHell is an open source Unix shell and command language.

fields.name: Haxe
fields.summary: Haxe is an open source statically-typed multi-paradigm programming language.

fields.name: Haskell
fields.summary: Haskell is a statically-typed functional paradigm language named after logician Haskell Curry.

fields.name: Go
fields.summary: Go is a strongly statically-typed, BSD-licensed open source language originally built at Google.

fields.name: Scala
fields.summary: Scala is a strongly statically-typed multi-paradigm (object-oriented and functional) language that compiles to Java bytecode to run on the Java Virtual Machine.

fields.name: Elm
fields.summary: Elm is a functional paradigm language intended for declaratively building web applications.

fields.name: JavaScript
fields.summary: JavaScript is a dynamically-typed interpreted language supported by all major web browsers and is increasingly used to write server-side web application code as well.

fields.name: Kotlin
fields.summary: Kotlin is a statically-typed language for the Java Virtual Machine that is open source under the Apache 2 license.

fields.name: D
fields.summary: D is a multi-paradigm (object-oriented, functional and generic) statically-typed language originally intended as a C++ replacement but has now developed beyond that original goal.

fields.name: Elixir
fields.summary: Elixir is a multi-paradigm (functional, distributed and process-oriented) dynamically-typed language that runs on the Erlang virtual machine. Elixir is open sourced under the Apache 2 license.

fields.name: Java
fields.summary: Java is an object-oriented paradigm, statically-typed language originally created with the goal for developers to write code once and run it on any platform the Java Virtual Machine (JVM) is available.

fields.name: Julia
fields.summary: Julia is a multi-paradigm (procedural, object-oriented and functional), dynamically-typed general purpose language often used for scientific computing.

fields.name: Logo
fields.summary: Logo is a dynamically-typed, functional and procedural paradigm educational language which is commonly known by the small robot on the screen called a "turtle" that is used for drawing.

fields.name: Lua
fields.summary: Lua is a dynamically-typed scripting language open sourced under the MIT license.

fields.name: Perl
fields.summary: Perl is a functional paradigm, dynamically-typed language open sourced under the GNU license. Perl 5 and Perl 6 are separate languages therefore Perl is sometimes referred to as "a family of programming languages" rather than a single entity.

fields.name: PHP
fields.summary: PHP, which currently stands for PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor, is a dynamically-typed scripting language typically used for server-side web development.

fields.name: Wolfram Language
fields.summary: The Wolfram Language is a dynamically-typed proprietary licensed language for mathematical computation. The language existed in some form for over 25 years before its official introduction in 2013.

fields.name: Groovy
fields.summary: Groovy is a dynamically-typed, object-oriented paradigm language that runs on the Java Virtual Machine and is open sourced under the Apache 2 license.

fields.name: Erlang
fields.summary: Erlang is a dynamically-typed, functional and concurrent paradigm often used for highly available and fault tolerant systems. Erlang is open sourced under the Apache 2 license.

fields.name: Laravel
fields.summary: The PHP Framework for Web Artisans
